[3] Ukraine
Date: Wed 17Oct 2018 
Source: The Koz Telegram [abridged, edited]
https://ktelegram.com/in-vinnytsia-region-the-measles-outbreak-two-schools-have-suspended-training-24-channel/46328/


In Sharhorod district, Vinnytsia region, there is a measles outbreak. Because of the high incidence in the villages Rakhny-Forest and Koesteren, 2 schools have stopped training. The measles outbreak was registered in the village of Rakhny-Forest in a secondary school. There on Wed 17 Sep [2018], 15 children were sick. Therefore, the local authorities decided to stop teaching in the school until 26 Oct 2018.

In addition, isolated cases of measles were recorded in the village of Koesteren. So, in one of the schools, restrictive measures were also introduced. However, in the laboratory center, there is no information about how long these measures will last.

"In Kapatiran, there are 6 sick children who are taught directly in school. In the locality as well as neighbouring villages also, there are cases of morbidity... In the village, there is an emergency situation," reported in the laboratory center.

In general, in the region of Vinnytsia in the past, there were 106 cases of measles, and this year [2018] -- already 1500 cases. In the Carpathian region, 3 rural schools were closed because of the outbreak of measles in the region. In particular, 2 schools in Nadvirna district also spent the rest of the week on a forced weekend break.

